'''closed book'''
# A person or thing that cannot be easily understood; someone or something [[uncomprehensible]] or [[puzzling]]
#:* ''"Her [[courteous]], [[sedate]], [[inexorable]] husband, whose [[will]] she could not [[bend]], whom she could not [[cajole]], whose mind was a [[closed book]] to her &mdash; a book which had lain by her hand for three years, which she had never had the [[curiosity]] to open!"'' &mdash; [[w:Prisoners|Prisoners]] by [[Mary Cholmondeley]]

